raw_data.title: IT Program Manager
raw_data.description: The IT Program Manager serves as senior corporate representative responsible for overall contract performance. Directly supervises a number of Technical Project Managers depending on scope/size of contract; directs all technical, financial management, and administrative activities; manages the schedule and budget; and provides technical, organizational, and business leadership as needed. Leads the program or multiple projects and is responsible for overall program performance, including cost, schedule, IT deliverables, and contractual compliance. Provides IT quality control and IT quality assurance for all IT deliverables while meeting program deadlines and budget constraints. Provides the interface to the customer and Technical Project Managers. Identifies, acquires, and utilizes company resources to achieve program/project objectives. May have additional subject matter expertise in information management, computer science, systems engineering, application engineering, software engineering, and/or information systems.

raw_data.title: Information Systems Auditor
raw_data.description: Performs information system audits within a variety of Defense and Civilian environments to assess the design and effectiveness of IT and security controls for/in critical information technology systems and processes. Develops, coordinates, and implements audit plans, manages the execution of audit test procedures, reviews and analyzes audit-derived evidence, evaluate controls and processes for compliance with policies, procedures, laws, and regulations and ensures conclusions are reached. Performs comprehensive technical assessments, as part of the audit(s), to detect technical control weaknesses and process improvement opportunities. The technical assessments may include, but shall not be limited to, reviewing Linux and Windows system logs, analyzing network traffic, inspecting web and application logs, and correlating events across various logging mechanisms to assess the effectiveness of organizational IT and security controls. The Information System Auditor, throughout these processes, prepares working papers, collaborates with customers and other team members, and leverages knowledge gained for the benefit of the customer and their audit objectives. Ensures that customers are provided with thorough post-audit guidance and findings, while further ensuring that measurable and achievable areas for improvement are identified in easy-to-understand layman terms.
